                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1031">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/3945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-06T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 6, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Your 83, June 5, noon. Mr. de la Rue has informed the Department that Haiti
                    requires no additional assistance during the present fiscal year and that he
                    will be able to draft a satisfactory budget provided that he can be assured of
                    an average Export-Import expenditure of $160,000 a month during the 1940–1
                    fiscal year. Under these circumstances, the Department agreed in principle to
                    whatever increase in the Export-Import credit may be necessary to permit the J.
                    G. White program<note n="9" xml:id="d1031fn1">A program of public works in
                        Haiti.</note> to continue through September, 1941 at the rate indicated. The
                    amount will be decided upon August 1 next.</p>
                <p>You may so inform President Vincent saying at the same time that in view of the
                    world coffee situation the Department trusts that the Haitian Government will be
                    willing to effect such economies as the present situation will probably require
                    in all coffee countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
